                    <h2>Actions to Consider</h2>
                     <ul>
            <li>Establish and communicate a vision for the cadence of your Pipeline Review calls, making sure that everyone is clear on the agenda, the preparation required, and the normal flow of the session.
</li>
            <li>
At a basic level, ensure that everyone on the team understands his Pipeline Goals by Revenue Type.  This should be the easiest thing to do, but it is nevertheless essential that each of the sellers can tell what they need in their pipeline, and how to assess the gap.

</li></ul>
                    <div class="more_info">
                    <ul>
            <li>Ensure that Managers and sellers are fully conversant with the rules that determine Active, Stalled and Inactive, as well as the elements have been defined for Opportunity Size Risk Analysis, i.e. Rocks, Stones and Pebbles. Ideally, there will have been some consultation prior to the configuration of Dealmaker Sales Performance Manager.

</li>
            <li>It is important that everyone understands the value of accurate data. Establish a weekly cadence whereby you can be sure that the data in your Pipeline is accurate. This will make the calls more efficient and both sellers and managers will consequently spend less time massaging the pipeline.
</li>
        </ul>
                    </div>
